      • addHeader

        public void addHeader()
        Adds the header data to the created report. All reports will follow the same concept. The report submitted to SilverSneakers for reimbursement must include facilities' name address, location id, and reporting month and year.

      • convertDate

        public void convertDate(java.lang.String date)
        The written report is saved to the users Desktop as (month)(year).xlsx.
        i.e., a report created in December 2018 would be saved as 'DECEMBER2018.xlsx'.

        convertDate is used to change the numerical date to alphabetical (i.e., '12' would be converted to 'DECEMBER').
        Parameters:
        date - - the previously formatted date as mm/dd/yy.

      • getTempFile

        public java.io.File getTempFile()
        The file is a temporary txt file that extracted data in the report saved from the membership system. Once the data is read from the file, written to the report, and the report is opened from the application, the file is deleted from the users Desktop.
        Returns:
        the temporary file that contains data extracted in the report that was saved from the membership system.
